# Blitzer CLI

A minimalist command-line tool for language text processing. Accepts text via stdin and outputs word lists via stdout.

## Installation

```bash
pip install -e .
```

## Usage

```bash
# Basic usage
echo "Your text here" | blitzer [language_code] [mode]

# With frequency counts
echo "Your text here" | blitzer pli word_list --freq

# Available languages: pli (Pali), slv (Slovenian)
# Available modes: word_list, lemma_list, word_list_context, lemma_list_context
```

## Configuration

The tool uses XDG specifications for configuration:
- Config file: `~/.config/blitzer/config.toml`
- Exclusion files: `~/.config/blitzer/[lang_code]_exclusion.txt`

## Features

- Minimalist design with clean output
- Language extensibility through plugin system
- Configurable defaults via XDG
- Same processing functionality as original Blitzer
